<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Is my Great Staff working?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Lemaitre">Lemaitre</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:05 a.m. 16/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Is my Great Staff working?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Could someone give me some insight on something...? I have been using a worn great staff (as a Erudite Wizard) from level 2-6 and while I was 6th I bought a Great Staff (not worn) to further inflict more damage. However, my max damage on the worn great staff (dam of 13) is the exact same I have been doing with the Great Staff (dam of 13 per hit). I don't understand this because the worn geat staff is worth a few gold and has a damage value on it of 6 whereas the Great Staff is worth 20pp and has a damage value of 9? Why is it that I am not doing more damage with a better weapon? They are both 2H Blunt so it's not like the skill changed with the weapons.

<P>TIA,
<BR>Lemaitre (Study of the Arcane Arts of Wizardry)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
